* 3.0 V / 2.0 V hysteretic threshold detector
* Requirement:
*   Output LOW -> HIGH when input rises above 3.0 V +/-0.1 V
*   Output HIGH -> LOW when input falls below 2.0 V +/-0.1 V
*
* Replacement comparator used:
*   LT1715 from LTC1.lib
*
* LT1715 pin order from provided symbol:
*   1 = In+
*   2 = In-
*   3 = Vcc
*   4 = Vee
*   5 = VS+
*   6 = GND
*   7 = OUT
*
* Single-supply connection used here:
*   Vcc  -> +5V
*   VS+  -> +5V
*   Vee  -> 0V
*   GND  -> 0V
*
* Hysteresis network:
*   R1, R2 create VREF = 2.50 V
*   R4 feeds VIN into the non-inverting node
*   R5 feeds back VOUT into the non-inverting node
*
* Threshold equation:
*   VIN(th) = VREF*(1 + R4/R5) - VOUT*(R4/R5)
*
* With:
*   R4 = 10.0k
*   R5 = 49.9k
*   VREF = 2.50V
*
* Expected thresholds:
*   Rising threshold  ~ 3.001 V when VOUT = 0 V
*   Falling threshold ~ 1.999 V when VOUT = 5 V

.lib LTC1.lib

.param VDDVAL=5.0
.param RREF_TOP=10k
.param RREF_BOT=10k
.param RIN=10k
.param RFB=49.9k

* 5 V supply
V1 VDD 0 {VDDVAL}

* Input waveform:
* 0 V -> 5 V in 10 ms, then 5 V -> 0 V in next 10 ms
* This lets us observe both thresholds in one run
VIN_SRC VIN 0 PWL(0 0 10m 5 20m 0)

* Reference divider: 5.0 V -> 2.50 V
R1 VDD VREF {RREF_TOP}
R2 VREF 0   {RREF_BOT}

* Hysteresis network
R4 VIN  NPLUS {RIN}
R5 VOUT NPLUS {RFB}

* Optional output load / pull-up from prior LM393-style design
* Keeps VOUT well-defined if needed by the macromodel and is only a light load otherwise
R3 VDD VOUT 10k

* Supply decoupling
C1 VDD 0 100n

* Comparator instance
* XU1 In+   In-   Vcc  Vee VS+ GND OUT  LT1715
XU1 NPLUS  VREF  VDD  0   VDD 0   VOUT LT1715

* DC operating point
.op

* Transient simulation
.tran 0 20m 0 100n

* Measurements
.meas op VREF_DC FIND V(VREF)

* Output switching point on the rising input sweep
.meas tran T_RISE  WHEN V(VOUT)=2.5 RISE=1
.meas tran VIN_RISE FIND V(VIN) AT=T_RISE

* Output switching point on the falling input sweep
.meas tran T_FALL  WHEN V(VOUT)=2.5 FALL=1
.meas tran VIN_FALL FIND V(VIN) AT=T_FALL

* Useful checkpoints
.meas tran VOUT_9MS  FIND V(VOUT) AT=9m
.meas tran VOUT_19MS FIND V(VOUT) AT=19m

.end
``
